sentences: John Thomas Brown (April 2, 1918 – November 24, 1969) was an American tenor saxophonist of the Chicago blues era.
He worked as a session musician for several artists and made some records on the Harlem label in the 1950s.
He appeared on several tracks of Fleetwood Mac's 1969 album Fleetwood Mac in Chicago/Blues Jam in Chicago, Vols.
He died in Chicago in November 1969, at the age of 51.
On May 14, 2011, the fourth annual White Lake Blues Festival took place at the Howmet Playhouse Theater in Whitehall, Michigan.
The event was a success, and a headstone was placed in June 2011.
